Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '244̣'. Name Dios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0344.36.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (137)
